Memory Card Game - Java
This is a simple implementation of a memory card game written in Java. In this game, players need to match pairs of cards by flipping them over two at a time. The game continues until all pairs have been matched.

How to Play
Compile and run the main class to start the game.
The game initializes a 4x4 grid of cards with hidden values.
Players take turns entering the coordinates of two cards they want to flip.
If the values on the flipped cards match, the cards remain face up.
If the values on the flipped cards don't match, the cards are flipped back face down.
Continue playing until all pairs are matched.

Usage
Clone or download the repository to your local machine.
Open the project in your Java development environment.
Compile and run the main class to start the game.

Features
Interactive command-line interface.
Random shuffling of card values for each game.
Simple logic for checking card matches.

Code Structure
main.java: Contains the main class with the game logic.
deckClass.java: Defines the deckClass class responsible for managing the deck of cards and their behavior.

Contributions
Contributions are welcome! If you'd like to improve the game or add new features, feel free to fork this repository, make your changes, and submit a pull request.
